cs.DC, cs.CC, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.AI 

This paper discusses scheduling strategies for cloud computing services, which involves distributed computing and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with the optimization of response times, which falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity and Cryptography). The use of analytical and computational techniques to evaluate the scheduling algorithms suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper mentions the use of AI techniques to prioritize requests, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
